description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a motivated &lt;strong&gt;Ward Manager (RMN/RNLD)&lt;/strong&gt; with a passion for delivering the best quality of care, to drive change, improve practice and be part of a hospital wide quality improvement project.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Department&lt;/strong&gt;: Adarna Ward - Male Autistic Spectrum Disorder (ASD). &lt;strong&gt;Adarna Ward &lt;/strong&gt;is our new 15 bed rehabilitation service, at Cygnet Hospital Wyke, for men with mental illness and a secondary diagnosis of autism spectrum disorder. The service is delivered in a purpose-built therapeutic environment, where the focus is on recovery through meaningful activity and engagement in local community initiatives. Our aim is to support service users to live as independently as possible.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary:&lt;/strong&gt;£42,000 per annum&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours: &lt;/strong&gt;37.5 hours per week (Monday to Friday; 9-5)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cygnet Hospital Wyke &lt;/strong&gt;is transforming. Committed to delivering safe, effective, person-centred care, we are looking to recruit experienced Registered Mental Health Nurses (RMN) and Registered Learning Disability Nurses (RNLD) who share our ambition to be outstanding.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We value our colleagues and provide a comprehensive range of wellbeing and professional development activities including:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Individual/group clinical supervision and de-briefing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Trauma informed care and psychological formulation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leadership and coaching&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cognitive Behavioural Therapy, Dialectical Behaviour Therapy, Schema Therapy and EMDR&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working closely with local universities, we are building a culture of clinical excellence with opportunities to undertake research in practice, evaluate latest evidence based interventions and deliver teaching/training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Cygnet? We’ll offer you…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS and employee discount scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;50% NMC registration renewal paid by Cygnet&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free meals on duty&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free parking&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;RCNi membership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Company paid Life Assurance scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Smart Health Toolkit- Providing you with Fitness Programmes, Nutrition consultation and Health checks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An experienced RMN or RNLD with a current Pin Number, you’ll have…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience at Clinical Team Leader level or above&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience/awareness ofAutistic Spectrum Disorder&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to maintain documentation, undertake audits &amp; demonstrate integrity in your role&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A good understanding of the latest nursing practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A commitment to patient recovery in order to effectively monitor, manage &amp; reduce risk&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Compassion, resilience &amp; a dedication to empower &amp; support service user independence&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Desirable:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Nurses with interests in leadership, research &amp; risk assessment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to deputise in the absence of the Clinical Manager&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Next steps…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Call us to find out more and discuss our exciting programme of development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You may like to visit, meet us and have a look around&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ready to make a positive change?&lt;/strong&gt; Please click on the ‘apply now’ link below.&lt;/p&gt;
